    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so if that's true, why do most economists say it's such a big risk for businesses in places like the midwest? it feels like there's a massive contradiction between how people talk about \"economic stimulus\" and how it actually plays out on the ground for a cafe owner.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
